'''Archaeological Recording Kit''' (ARK) is a [[Web application|web-based]], [[Open-source software|open source]] software package for recording and disseminating [[Archaeology|archaeological]] data.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://ark.lparchaeology.com/|title=ARK|last=|first=|date=|website=L-P Archaeology|publisher=|access-date=2016-08-01}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.bajr.org/bajrresources/software.asp|title=Archaeology Software|last=Connolly|first=David|date=|website=BAJR|publisher=|access-date=2016-08-01}}</ref> ARK is primarily designed for recording [[Excavation (archaeology)|excavations]], but can also be used for [[Archaeological field survey|archaeological surveys]], [[Paleoecology|palaeoenvironmental research]] and [[Collections management (museum)|collections management]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.collectionstrust.org.uk/item/1066-archaeological-recording-kit-ark|title=Archaeological Recording Kit (ARK)|last=Poole|first=Nick|date=|website=Collections Trust|publisher=|language=en-gb|access-date=2016-08-01}}</ref>

ARK is based on the [[LAMP (software bundle)|LAMP stack]] and [[MapServer]], and is [[free software]] released under the [[GNU GPL]].<ref>http://sourceforge.net/projects/arkdb/</ref> It was developed by L-P Archaeology, a British [[commercial archaeology]] practice.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.lparchaeology.com/cms/about-lp|title=About L-P|last=|first=|date=|website=L-P Archaeology|publisher=|access-date=2016-08-01}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.archaeologists.net/ro/484-l-p-archaeology|title=L - P : Archaeology|last=|first=|date=|website=Chartered Institute for Archaeologists|publisher=|access-date=2016-08-01}}</ref>

The [[Fasti Online]] project was built using an ARK back-end, and demonstrates its usage beyond normal archaeological recording.<ref>http://www.fastionline.org</ref>

