A '''corynebacteriophage''' is a DNA-containing [[bacteriophage]] specific for [[corynebacteria]]. It introduces toxigenicity into strains of ''[[Corynebacterium diphtheriae]]''.<ref>{{cite book|title=Stedman's Medical Dictionary|editor=Julie K. Segman|publisher=Lippincott Williams & Wilkins|location=Baltimore, Maryland|year=2006|edition=28th|pages=449|isbn=978-0-7817-3390-8}}</ref>

